        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-05-11 14:32:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nIf Response.Status.fromStatusCode(statusCode) returns null then MDC.put(someKey, null) will throw a NPE.\n\nThe method setErrorDesc might hit this same issue as setResponseDescription. Can we patch both?\n\nIn the new code if CustomResponseStatus returns null then MDC.put(someKey, null) will throw a NPE.\n\nBefore MDC.put can we check if the value is null? If it is null use the value Constants.DefaultValues.UNKNOWN.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "ad14ed97f9f9e9d4859a5b413578f1d6cda9df2a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1219,
          "name": "Kevin Smokowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "kevin.smokowski@att.com",
          "username": "nullop"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-05-11 14:35:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nShould we map any other WEBDAV codes? https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Status https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/ws/rs/core/Response.Status.html",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "407c9ad530cc3ba76fbb9bba99cdd7731f2d3eeb",
        "author": {
