          "username": "cdgasparini"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-05-11 15:07:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Patch Set 4:\n> \n> If Response.Status.fromStatusCode(statusCode) returns null then MDC.put(someKey, null) will throw a NPE.\n> \n> The method setErrorDesc might hit this same issue as setResponseDescription. Can we patch both?\n> \n> In the new code if CustomResponseStatus returns null then MDC.put(someKey, null) will throw a NPE.\n> \n> Before MDC.put can we check if the value is null? If it is null use the value Constants.DefaultValues.UNKNOWN.\n\nI didnt notice setResponseDescription, let me fix it as well.\nIf CustomResponseStatus returns null, IllegalArgumentException will be thrown. We will never arrive to \nMDC.put, seems that you are seeing different code than the commited",
        "patchset_number": 4
